WEBVTT

Title
00:00.100 --> 00:04.000    line:10%
<c.main>How To Make 
Japanese Style Egg Mayo Sadwich</c>

Subtitle
00:06.000 --> 00:12.000     line:80% 
Put 3 eggs to a medium sauce pan

00:13.000 --> 00:16.000     line:95% 
Add water till fully covered the eggs

00:17.800 --> 00:23.500     line:80%
Bring to boil

00:21.500 --> 00:24.000     line:95%
Once boiled, cooked the eggs for 12 minutes

00:24.500 --> 00:27.500     line:95%
Then, transfer the eggs to ice water

00:28.000 --> 00:36.000     line:70%
Once the eggs is cooled, peel the egg shells

00:32.500 --> 00:36.000     line:80%
transfer to another bowl

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000     line:70%
Prepare 4 slices of bread

00:39.500 --> 00:45.000     line:80%
Spread with butter

00:46.000 --> 00:54.500     line:95%
Mashed the eggs with fork

00:55.500 --> 00:58.000     line:95%
Add 1/4 teaspoon of sugar

00:58.500 --> 01:02.000     line:95%
Add 1/4 teaspoon of salt

01:02.000 --> 01:04.200    line:80%
Add some black pepper

01:05.500 --> 01:08.000     line:80%
Add 2 teaspoon of milk

01:08.800 --> 01:12.000     line:75%
Add 2 tablespoon of Japanese mayonaisse

01:12.500 --> 01:21.000     line:95%
Mixed well

01:21.500 --> 01:26.000     line:80%
(Taste and add more salt or black pepper if needed)

01:27.000 --> 01:43.000     line:95%
Spread the egg salad on the bread

01:44.000 --> 01:50.000     line:95%
Cover with the other slice of bread

01:51.000 --> 02:00.500     line:95%
Place between two plates
and set aside for 5 minutes

02:04.000 --> 02:15.000     line:95%
Cut off all sides of the bread 

02:15.500 --> 02:22.000     line:95%
Cut the sandwich into half

Ending      
02:23.000 --> 02:43.000     line:95%
Serve and Enjoy!
